**Kisspeptin 5mg  
Instructions for Use  
**Medication Class: Reproductive health and hormonal regulation peptide

  
Indication: In women it is used to maintain regular menstrual cycles as well as to stimulate ovulation in cases of PCOS. In men it is used to stimulate the production of endogenous testosterone in men with secondary hypogonadism.  
  
**Medication Details  
**• 5 mg vial  
• Bacteriostatic Water 2 mL  
• Concentration: 0.025 mg per unit  
  
**Dosing 10 units every other day for 40 days. One month on/one month off**

consult your prescribing Healthcare Provider for ongoing monitoring of treatment

**Storage & Handling  
**• Refrigerate after reconstitution (36°F–46°F / 2°C–8°C)  
• Do not freeze. Protect from light  
• Discard after 90 days  
**Missed Dose  
**• Take within 5 days if remembered  
• If more than 5 days, skip and resume weekly schedule  
• Do not double dose  
**Injection Technique (Summary)  
**• Inject subcutaneously into abdomen, thigh, or upper arm  
• Rotate injection sites  
• Clean site, pinch skin, inject at 90° angle  
• Dispose of syringe in sharps container
